      • isRoutable

        public boolean isRoutable(RouteNode rn,
                          int depth)
        Looks backwards from an input pin depth number of hops to see if there exists at least one free path.
        Parameters:
        p - Input pin to check routability
        depth - Number of PIP hops to check
        Returns:
        True if there exists at least one path depth PIP hops free, false otherwise.

      • reserveCriticalNodes

        public void reserveCriticalNodes()
        Certain input pins in a switch box can also serve as a bounce. We need to prevent the usage of the bounce if the pin will be need to route an input pin. This method reserves those wires by marking them used. They are later released as the routing for that particular net is starting.

      • reserveCriticalNodes

        public void reserveCriticalNodes(ArrayList<SitePinInst> sitePinInsts)

      • markExistingRouteResourcesUsed

        public void markExistingRouteResourcesUsed()
        This router will preserve all existing routes (even partials) intact. This method will mark them as used to avoid route conflicts.

      • routePinsReEntrant

        public void routePinsReEntrant(ArrayList<SitePinInst> sitePinInsts,
                               boolean routeUnroutedNets)
        This is a specialized routing function that will only route the pins given. It is assumed that each pin provided already belongs to a net. If any PIPs have already been used on the net, they can be leveraged on this route.
        Parameters:
        sitePinInsts - The sink pins to be routed.
